<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="821" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d821">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 841.731/63</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<hi rend="italic"><persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="to">Page</persName></hi>)</head>
                        <dateline>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-12">
                                <hi rend="italic">November 12, 1914</hi>.</date>
                        </dateline>
                        <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                        <p>523. From Copenhagen, 11th. Danish firms conducting business with
                            American houses protest against English censorship of open commercial
                            cables, which is ruining business between America and Denmark. Please
                            present this matter to Foreign Office with a view to ameliorating the
                            hardships described.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_BWJ1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>